RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Workflow automation (primary)

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Parent enquiry follow-up, occupancy tracking, EYFS observation logging, staff ratio compliance, Ofsted evidence prep, invoicing/funding claims, and recruitment DBS/onboarding.

UK AI ADOPTION (use in conversation):
Barclays Business Prosperity Index (Aug 2025): 89% of UK businesses plan AI use within two years; SMEs (10–49 staff) averaged £125k AI investment vs £400k for 250+ employee firms. Lloyds Business Barometer (Mar 2026): 66% have invested in AI, mostly under £25k—39% cite AI/digital skills shortage. Nursery groups digitised registers but AI for parent comms, staffing forecasts, and observation drafting is rare outside national chains.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA not lead for safeguarding-sensitive parent comms—automate enquiries and funding admin; train managers on AI observation drafts.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Automate parent enquiry nurture
• AI occupancy and staffing forecasts
• Ofsted evidence collation training

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• How much time does the team spend on the highest-volume admin tasks in nursery / early years groups (private)?
• Have they piloted AI tools internally, or only client-facing tech?
• Who owns operations/process improvement — and is AI training on anyone''s KPIs?
• What would ''win'' look like in 90 days: hours saved, fewer errors, or staff confident using AI?

NOTES:
Revenue/employee figures are estimates for sizing only — confirm on Companies House before quoting.
Research date: 2026-06-23. Validate website and decision-maker before outreach.

