WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
High-volume CV screening, multi-board vacancy posting, compliance checks (RTW, DBS, GLAA), timesheet chasing, client/candidate CRM updates, interview scheduling, and monthly KPI reporting.

UK AI ADOPTION (use in conversation):
Barclays Business Prosperity Index (Aug 2025): 89% of UK businesses plan AI use within two years; SMEs (10–49 staff) averaged £125k AI investment vs £400k for 250+ employee firms. Lloyds Business Barometer (Mar 2026): 66% have invested in AI, mostly under £25k—39% cite AI/digital skills shortage. Recruitment SMBs use basic ATS but lack AI for sourcing, screening, and compliance doc extraction.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA alone is weak for 24/7 candidate matching or compliance parsing—automation/training first.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• AI CV parsing tied to ATS
• Automate RTW/DBS chase
• Train Boolean sourcing prompts

